**who —** METROID — the seventh lineage — the second game-world

**what —** The Metroid universe — the lonely, interconnected world you explore alone, the bio-mechanical tyrant Mother Brain, the life-draining creatures, and the silent hunter who maps it all.

**where —** planet Zebes and the Space Pirate war — Crateria, Brinstar, Norfair, Maridia, Tourian; the 8-bit original and its SNES masterpiece  Framework inputs: Metroid; Super Metroid; the Chozo; the Metroids; planet Zebes  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0 · Universe David 0)

**why —** A lone hunter in alien armor descends into a living world to end the Metroid menace — and the last of them dies to save her.

**how —** Crystallized from Metroid (NES, 1986) and Super Metroid (SNES, 1994).

**◌ the mythos —** A lone hunter in alien armor descends into a living world to end the Metroid menace — and the last of them dies to save her. Two games, one hunter — and the reveal, in 1986, that she is a woman.

**the moniker —** ⟦METROID:MET:4da19c⟧ · spoken *steth-nae-stein*

**the seal —** A lone hunter in Chozo armor descends to end the Metroids — and the last of them gives its life to save her.

> *the asterisk, kept visible —* an emergent here is a named axiom of the framework (its mythos,
